sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP (internal)
    participant PyPI as pypi.org<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 1: User Accesses Workbench via Browser

    User->>Router: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{username}<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward to oauth-proxy<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS1.2+

    alt Not authenticated
        OAuthProxy->>User: 302 Redirect to OAuth login
        User->>OAuthServer: Login request<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+
        OAuthServer-->>User: OAuth token
        User->>OAuthProxy: Request with OAuth token<br/>HTTPS/8443
    end

    OAuthProxy->>OAuthServer: Validate token<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+
    OAuthServer-->>OAuthProxy: Token valid, user identity
    OAuthProxy->>Jupyter: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8888 (internal, no auth)
    Jupyter-->>OAuthProxy: JupyterLab UI HTML
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: Response with session cookie
    Router-->>User: HTTPS response TLS1.2+<br/>Session established

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Install Python Package from Workbench

    User->>Jupyter: Execute: pip install pandas<br/>via Terminal WebSocket
    Jupyter->>PyPI: GET /simple/pandas<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
    PyPI-->>Jupyter: Package metadata
    Jupyter->>PyPI: Download wheel file<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
    PyPI-->>Jupyter: pandas-*.whl
    Jupyter->>Jupyter: Install to workbench filesystem<br/>UID 1001 permissions
    Jupyter-->>User: Installation complete

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Load Data from S3 in Notebook

    User->>Jupyter: Execute notebook cell:<br/>s3.get_object(Bucket, Key)
    Jupyter->>S3: GET /bucket/model-data<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>Jupyter: Object data stream
    Jupyter-->>User: Data loaded into DataFrame

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Run kubectl command from Workbench

    User->>Jupyter: Execute: kubectl get pods<br/>via Terminal
    Jupyter->>K8sAPI: GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/pods<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Jupyter: Pod list JSON
    Jupyter-->>User: Pod list displayed

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 5: Elyra Pipeline Execution (Runtime Image)

    User->>Jupyter: Submit Elyra pipeline
    Jupyter->>K8sAPI: Create pipeline run<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Schedule runtime pod<br/>Image: odh-pipeline-runtime-*
    Note over K8sAPI: Runtime pod executes<br/>Python script with ML code
    K8sAPI->>S3: Load input data<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>AWS credentials from secret
    S3-->>K8sAPI: Input data
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Execute ML training
    K8sAPI->>S3: Save model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Jupyter: Pipeline step completed
    Jupyter-->>User: Pipeline success notification
